No I don’t.  You are saying that good solid linear logic is equally as bad as unsound, irrational circular logic.  There is no point there to see.  That’s just dumb.  If I disagree with you for believing something because god says so, and I do it based on lack of evidentiary support for god’s existence, that is solid, sound reasoning.  Just the same as if you claimed little green men told you or that your dog wrote it in the snow with his pee.  Try this, if you disbelieve that your child caught botulism from eating undercooked red meat because he never ate any red meat, you are using sound logic.  If you disbelieve your child caught botulism from eating warm sugar because botulism can’t survive in sugar concentrate, you’d be using sound logic.  If you disbelieve your child caught botulism from eating your cooking because you are his mom and no mom would give her child botulism, that is flawed. <br>
<br>
Here is the crux of it, you don’t like it because it invalidates your position.  You equate it to something you think we don’t like and expect us to agree.  Important differences being that what you think we don’t like doesn’t invalidate my position, nor is it solid logic so we don’t really care either way.  You are making the extreme claims, therefore you need to provide evidentiary support for your claims.  Lacking that you have nothing to debate and no purpose here as this IS a debate board.<br>
